# .eslintignore Template

## Purpose

Exclude files and directories from ESLint linting. Prevents linting of generated code, dependencies, and non-JavaScript files.

## Official Documentation

- [ESLint - Ignoring Code](https://eslint.org/docs/latest/use/configure/ignore) - Official guide
- [Flat Config ignores](https://eslint.org/docs/latest/use/configure/configuration-files#ignoring-files) - ESLint 9+ approach

## When to Use

- ✅ JavaScript/TypeScript projects using ESLint
- ✅ Projects with generated code that shouldn't be linted
- ✅ Monorepos with mixed content

## When NOT to Use

- ❌ Non-JavaScript projects
- ❌ Projects not using ESLint
- ❌ ESLint 9+ flat config (use `ignores` in config instead)

## Required Marker Files

- `package.json` with ESLint dependency
- `.eslintrc.*` or `eslint.config.js`

## Trade-offs & Alternatives

| Alternative | When to Use Instead |
|-------------|---------------------|
| `ignores` in flat config | ESLint 9+ (recommended) |
| `ignorePatterns` in config | ESLint 8.x config-based ignore |
| `/* eslint-disable */` | Single file exceptions |

## ESLint 9+ Note

ESLint 9+ uses flat config and the `ignores` property:

```javascript
// eslint.config.js
export default [
  {
    ignores: [
      "dist/",
      "node_modules/",
      "coverage/",
      "*.config.js"
    ]
  },
  // ... other config
];
```

If using ESLint 9+, prefer this approach over `.eslintignore`.

## Template (.eslintignore)

```gitignore
# =============================================================================
# .eslintignore - <PROJECT_NAME>
# =============================================================================

# === Build Output ===
dist/
build/
out/
.next/
.nuxt/
.output/

# === Dependencies ===
node_modules/

# === Generated Files ===
*.min.js
*.bundle.js
*.generated.*
coverage/

# === Config Files ===
# Usually don't need linting
*.config.js
*.config.mjs
*.config.cjs

# === Type Declarations ===
*.d.ts

# === Vendor/Third-Party ===
vendor/
public/vendor/
static/vendor/

# === Test Fixtures ===
# Files that intentionally have lint errors for testing
__fixtures__/
test/fixtures/

# === Documentation Examples ===
# Code examples that may not follow all rules
docs/examples/

# <PROJECT_SPECIFIC_IGNORES>
```

