## ESLint Flat Config Equivalent

If migrating to ESLint 9+ flat config:

```javascript
// eslint.config.js
import js from "@eslint/js";

export default [
  {
    // Global ignores (replaces .eslintignore)
    ignores: [
      // Build output
      "dist/**",
      "build/**",
      ".next/**",

      // Dependencies
      "node_modules/**",

      // Generated
      "*.min.js",
      "coverage/**",

      // Config files (optional)
      "*.config.js",

      // Type declarations
      "**/*.d.ts",
    ]
  },
  js.configs.recommended,
  // ... other config
];
```

## Validation Commands

```bash
# Check what files ESLint will lint
npx eslint --debug . 2>&1 | grep "Processing"

# Lint specific file to test ignore
npx eslint path/to/file.js

# List files that would be linted
npx eslint . --ext .js,.ts --format json | jq '.[].filePath'
```

## Inline Disable Comments

For single-file exceptions within non-ignored code:

```javascript
/* eslint-disable */
// Entire file ignored

/* eslint-disable no-console */
// Specific rule disabled for file

// eslint-disable-next-line no-console
console.log("This line only");
```

## Integration Notes

- `.eslintignore` uses gitignore syntax
- Patterns are relative to `.eslintignore` location
- `node_modules/` is ignored by default (don't need to add)
- Files in `.gitignore` are NOT automatically ignored by ESLint
- Consider syncing patterns with `.prettierignore`
